I gather up 10 people I know.  Not neceassirly my best friends, just casual acquantances with no history of being categorically insane or pathological liars.  In other words, average people.  They also have no direct link to one another.  I hand them each one copy photograph that I haven't looked at myself.  It's a little fuzzy, so details are hard to make out.  I ask them to describe it.<br>
<br>
First one says 'It's a lady pushing a stroller'<br>
2nd is 'It's a homeless person pushing a cart'<br>
3rd says 'it's some guy mowing the lawn'<br>
4th states that it's someone shopping at the supermarket<br>
<br>
and so on in that manner until all 10 descriptions have been received.  No 2 descriptions are exactly alike.  So I don't know EXACTLY what the photo is a picture of.  But I can tell that the photo is of a person pushing some object.  If I add and 11th person who says that their interpretation of the photo  is that it's a UFO abducting a cow (or if said person was the first opinion and the other 10 follow), it's a little noise in the process, but I'm still gonna think that the photo is someone pushing an object.<br>
<br>
